---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";

const title = "If I Pay $250 Extra on My Mortgage (what changes?)";
const description =
  "Paying an extra $250 toward principal can shorten payoff time and reduce total interest. Learn how to model it and what to confirm with your lender. Educational use only.";
---
<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} canonicalPath="/guides/pay-250-extra-on-mortgage" robots="noindex, follow">
  <section class="card hero">
    <span class="pill">Guide</span>
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <a href="/">Home</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <a href="/guides">Guides</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true">/</span>
      <span aria-current="page">Pay $250 extra</span>
    </nav>
    <h1>If I pay $250 extra on my mortgage, what happens?</h1>
    <p>
      A $250 monthly extra principal payment can meaningfully reduce total interest over time, especially when made consistently and
      applied as principal-only. This guide shows the workflow to estimate the impact and avoid common posting pitfalls.
    </p>
    <div class="btn-row">
      <a class="btn" href="/topics/mortgage-payoff">Mortgage payoff topic hub</a>
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/calculators/extra-payment-calculator">Model $250 extra</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/guides/calculate-mortgage-payoff-with-additional-principal-payments">Payoff workflow</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="grid" style="margin-top:18px">
    <div class="card section prose col-6">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">How to model it</h2>
      <ol class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
        <li>Enter principal, rate, and term.</li>
        <li>Set monthly extra to $250.</li>
        <li>Compare baseline vs extra (payoff time and total interest).</li>
      </ol>
    </div>
    <div class="card section prose col-6">
      <h2 style="margin-top:0">Try nearby amounts</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
        If $250 is close to your budget limit, test $200 and $300 to see how sensitive your payoff time is to the extra amount.
      </p>
      <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:12px">
        <a class="btn" href="/guides/pay-200-extra-on-mortgage">Pay $200 extra</a>
        <a class="btn" href="/guides/pay-300-extra-on-mortgage">Pay $300 extra</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">What to confirm with your lender</h2>
    <ul class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0; padding-left:18px">
      <li>Extra is applied as <strong>principal-only</strong> (not "paid ahead").</li>
      <li>No prepayment penalty applies.</li>
      <li>How extra payments are posted (timing affects interest slightly).</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Quick way to estimate impact</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      Compare your monthly interest (balance x rate / 12) to $250. If interest is much higher, early months benefit more.
      Use the calculator for exact payoff timing and interest savings.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Make the extra sustainable</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      A $250 extra can speed up payoff, but only if it fits your ongoing budget. Automate the payment and revisit after large expense
      changes so you can avoid stop-and-start patterns.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Monthly extra vs lump sum</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      A lump sum early can save more interest than the same total spread out. Compare $250 monthly to a one-time principal payment using
      the <a href="/calculators/additional-principal-payment-calculator">additional principal calculator</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">If you plan to refinance or move</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      If you expect to move within a few years, compare interest saved over that window instead of the full term. Extra payments can
      still help, but the benefit is smaller when you sell early.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">If you might pause the extra later</h2>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:10px 0 0">
      Run a second scenario where you stop the $250 after 12-24 months. This shows how much of the benefit depends on staying consistent.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="card section prose" style="margin-top:18px">
    <h2 style="margin-top:0">Next steps</h2>
    <div class="btn-row" style="margin-top:10px">
      <a class="btn btn-primary" href="/calculators/additional-principal-payment-calculator">Monthly vs lump sum</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/guides/amortization-with-extra-payments">Amortization with extra payments</a>
      <a class="btn" href="/guides/biweekly-vs-extra-principal">Biweekly vs extra principal</a>
    </div>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0">Educational use only. Not financial advice.</p>
    <p class="muted" style="margin:12px 0 0; font-size:13px">Last updated: 2026-01-24</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
